title: Nuclear charge dispersion in the fission of Np-237 by protons of medium energy.

x4freetext: Nuclear charge dispersion in the fission of Np-237
by protons of medium energy.

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Journal of Inorganic and Nuclear Chemistry, Vol.34, p.3323 (1972)

x4freetext: Np-237 was obtained in the form of Np-O(2). Its assay
was given as 99.29% Np and 0.12% total plutonium. The
materials was used without further purification.
A NaI(Tl) scintillation crystal was used for
activity measurements of Cu-64 and Ba-140.
.A 30 cm**3 Ge(Li) detector.
The target was prepared by mixing thoroughly
equimolar quantities of the neptunium and copper
oxides.
The duration of bombardment was 20 min.  The
beam current was of the order of 0.5 mu-A.
All the irradiations were performed in the
internal circulating proton beam.
Tbl.3 from JIN,34,3323,1972
The errors were estimated from
the uncertainties in decay curve analyses, counting
efficiencies and chemical yields.
Last checking has been done.
DATE is corrected
SD: REACTION code corrected in Subent 7.
- By Authors - The Activity of Cs-129 was Determined by
X-Ray Measurements Measured by Scintillation
Spectrometer. The Decay Curve from X-Ray Data were
Resolved Into Half-Life Components of 32.4 Hours from
Cs-129, 6.5 Days from Cs-132, 9.7 Days from Cs-131,
12.9 Days from Cs-136-G.  A Fluorescence Yield of
0.87 was Used For Calculating the Abundance of X-Rays
And L/K Ratio was Taken As 0.12 Independent of Decay
Energy.
